Test Name: MAYOCOMPLETE Renal Cell Carcinoma with Fibromyomatous Stroma Panel, Next-Generation Sequencing (Tumor)
Specimen Type: Formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tumor tissue or unstained tissue slides
Purpose: To perform next-generation sequencing to detect clinically significant genetic variants in renal cell carcinoma with fibromyomatous stroma.
Container: FFPE tissue block or set of unstained glass slides (10 slides, 5–10 µm sections)
Equipment: Validated high-throughput NGS platform (e.g., Illumina sequencer) and associated library preparation system
